\description{
Converts SnpEff-annotated, single-sample germline VCFs (GATK HaplotypeCaller ->
CNN tranches -> SnpEff, hg38) into a tabular variant table and returns it as
an in-memory \code{data.table} for downstream filtering (\code{\link[=gvr_filter]{gvr_filter()}}) and
summarisation (\code{\link[=gvr_summary]{gvr_summary()}}). In folder mode it finds every per-sample VCF,
converts each, and row-binds them into one combined gvr table. Emits the SAME
canonical 80-field schema as \code{\link[=read.gvr]{read.gvr()}} so downstream code is annotator-
agnostic. The conversion uses base R + \pkg{data.table} only - no external
annotation-package dependency.

This function is the SnpEff sibling of \code{\link[=read.gvr]{read.gvr()}} (VEP-annotated VCFs).
Both readers are usually invoked through \code{\link[=read.gvr]{read.gvr()}}, which auto-routes
SnpEff inputs to this function via the nested \code{.detect_annotator()} helper.
Calling \code{read.gvr.snpeff()} directly is supported for fully SnpEff-only
pipelines.
}
\details{
Output and behaviour:
\itemize{
\item Returns the final tabular variant \code{data.table}, one row per variant ALLELE
(multi-allelic sites are split). Multiple \code{ANN} annotation blocks per
allele are reduced to one most-severe transcript per allele.
\item Columns include the canonical MAF-style core fields (Hugo_Symbol, Variant_Classification, Start_Position, Reference_Allele, Tumor_Seq_Allele2, Tumor_Sample_Barcode, HGVSp_Short, IMPACT), the canonical 80 VEP CSQ field
names (populated from the equivalent SnpEff ANN fields where available;
blank for fields SnpEff does not supply), and key GATK QC fields.
\code{FILTER} is retained as a column and ALL variants (PASS and non-PASS) are
kept.
\item \code{Tumor_Seq_Allele1}/\code{Tumor_Seq_Allele2} are zygosity-aware (vcf2maf-
style), and an optional \code{Genotype} column (\code{Tumor_Seq_Allele1/Tumor_Seq_Allele2},
e.g. \code{"T/C"}) is added next to the alleles.
\item Each variant keeps its source sample in \code{Tumor_Sample_Barcode}.
\item Absent values are written as the empty string \code{""} (not \code{NA});
downstream \code{\link[=gvr_filter]{gvr_filter()}} / \code{\link[=gvr_summary]{gvr_summary()}} treat \code{NA} and \code{""} identically
as "missing".
\item Output is tagged with \code{attr(gvr, "annotator") = "snpeff"} so downstream
code can distinguish the source.
}

SnpEff-specific notes:
\itemize{
\item The nested \code{.detect_annotator()} helper inspects \verb{##INFO=<ID=*} header
lines and returns \code{"snpeff"} when \verb{##INFO=<ID=ANN} is found (and \code{"vep"}
when \verb{##INFO=<ID=CSQ} is found). If both are present, VEP takes priority.
\item The nested \code{get_ann_fields()} helper parses SnpEff's ANN INFO header
line, extracting the \code{'F1 | F2 | ... | FN'} field-name vector from inside
the single-quoted \verb{Description=} block.
\item The nested \code{.snpeff_strip_allele()} helper handles SnpEff's two
non-standard allele forms (Cingolani spec): cancer-somatic-vs-germline
(\code{"G-C"} -> \code{"G"}) and compound (\code{"C-chr1:123456_A>T"} -> \code{"C"}).
Standard ALT alleles (no dash) pass through unchanged.
\item Population AF columns (\code{gnomADe_AF}, etc.) are populated from the first
matching SnpEff ANN-side INFO key in \code{.AF_FIELDS_SNPEFF} (case-sensitive,
first match wins). Bare \code{AF} is intentionally excluded - in the VCF spec
it is the per-ALT caller frequency, not a population frequency.
}

Processing options (same as \code{\link[=read.gvr]{read.gvr()}}):
\itemize{
\item MULTI-FILE: in folder mode, every file matching \code{pattern} (default
\code{"*_NN.vcf.gz"}) is converted and row-bound.
\item HGVS CLEANUP (\code{strip_hgvs_prefix}): strips the Ensembl feature prefix
from \code{HGVSc}/\code{HGVSp} (e.g. \code{"ENST00000831140.1:n.1889G>A"} ->
\code{"n.1889G>A"}).
\item DEDUP (\code{dedup_columns}): removes duplicate-named columns ONLY when
their values are byte-for-byte identical across all rows (otherwise keeps
+ warns).
\item ABraOM (\code{add_abraom}): joins the Brazilian ABraOM SABE-609 allele
frequency as the \code{ABraOM_AF} column (downloaded/cached from \code{abraom_url}).
\item GENOTYPE-QUALITY FILTER (\code{min_DP}/\code{min_GQ}): keeps a record iff
\code{DP > min_DP} AND \code{GQ > min_GQ}; mirrors
\verb{bcftools view -e 'FORMAT/DP<=X | FORMAT/GQ<=Y'}. Set either to \code{NULL} to
disable that field; set both to \code{NULL} to disable the genotype filter
entirely.
\item GENE SUBSET (\code{genes}): restrict to a set of \code{Hugo_Symbol}s (exact,
case-insensitive).
}
}
